Oh been out fighting like with other boys. See and I - he must have hurt the other boy and the other boy came and told Hal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid808626 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15288751\charrsid8333642 
Did you and your husband bring the children to take up for themselves if somebody else struck them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11697723 PM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15288751\charrsid8333642 
Oh yes. Oh yes, but they were very friendly children. They were, and I never - all the time we lived in - Bute - in Plymouth, and we lived there for thirty-three years and - and a half, I never had - a complaint from any neighbour - about
 the behaviour of my children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid808626 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15288751\charrsid8333642 
How much did your husband have to do with your children when they were babies under a year?
