 called, lived at Creege Brawse. But he really wasn't what I call a good teacher. Because you see - he taught us - the scales you see are really the beginning of music aren't they. Well he taught us our scales, well instead of them - going on to - scale w
o
rk, what I call you know - he put us - well he used to bring every - nearly every week a big piece - a beautiful piece, well of course we weren't prepared for that really. And he kept brining these - and he used to charge mother two shillings a copy, I sh
