h's agent - called at the house to collect what they call - what do the call it - some - some death duties or something - or it is - there's a word, I don't know what it is, anyway - she said - the old lady lived in a cottage on the Terrace, so she said -
 
would you like to come up and see the old lady, she said, see where she lived. So she took him up and the old lady was laying in her coffin. And he demanded a hundred and fifty pound I think it - dilapidation, that's the word, dilapidation, and he demande
d - she had only a little four roomed cottage, he demanded of her a hundred and fifty pound dilapidation. And she took him up to the cottage, took him into the little room and pointed to her mother, and h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14175119\charrsid8333642 e'd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15288751\charrsid8333642  said, there's the dilapidation you'll have and all you'll have. No matter what you claim.

